points above the Treasury's 10-year note. Rated single-A-1 by
Moody's and single-A-plus by S&amp;P, the issue will be sold
through underwriters led by First Boston Corp.
   Cardinal Distribution Inc. -- $70 million of subordinated
debentures, due July 1, 2015, was priced at par to yield
7.25%. The debentures are convertible into the company's
common stock at $34.20 a share. Rated Ba-2 by Moody's and
double-B-minus by S&amp;P, the issue will be sold through
underwriters led by Smith Barney, Harris Upham &amp; Co.
                                                                                                       

