<LP>
   Algemene Bank Nederland N.V. and Amsterdam-Rotterdam Bank
N.V. said they reached a definitive agreement to merge and
predicted flat combined earnings this year.
   The two banks, which in March said they were discussing a
merger, plan to create a new institution, ABN Amro Holding
N.V. Based on current share prices, the new banking company
would have a stock market value of about 9.3 billion guilders
